  "market_context": "Intraday session on March 10, 2023: London manipulation above midnight open formed the daily wick; New York session distributed lower, targeting -2.5 and -4.5 standard deviations from the manipulation leg.",
  "key_observation": "The manipulation leg (London high above midnight open) created the daily candle's upper wick, and distribution occurred downward into -2.5 and -4.5 standard deviation zones, with a box setup entry at retest of the deviation range.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the manipulation leg as the London high above midnight open (pink rectangle ~15000–15040), which would form the daily candle's wick.",
    "Step 2: Applied standard deviation projections from the manipulation low to define distribution targets at -2.5σ (~14840) and -4.5σ (~14660).",
    "Step 3: Recognized the box setup opportunity at retest of the deviation zone (near 14870–14880), coinciding with an OTE zone and FVG support.",
    "Step 4: Observed price retracing into the FVG and up-close candles after the initial drop, confirming distribution and enabling short entry.",
    "Step 5: Tracked price reaching the -4 to -4.5σ target (~14660), completing the daily candle body with minimal further expansion."
  ],
  "outcome": "Short trade executed at retest of deviation/box zone (~14870), targeting -4.5σ (~14660); daily candle closed with full body in distribution, achieving ~2.1R+ move.",
  "lessons": "Standard deviation projections anchored to the manipulation leg provide precise distribution targets; box setups at retests of deviation zones offer high-probability entries when aligned with FVGs and OTE zones within the AMD framework.",
